The paper discusses the use of magneto-inductive communication transceivers for simultaneous wireless information and power transfer (SWIPT) in an energy harvesting network, which involves communication and signal processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also focuses on the Internet-of-Things (IoT) architecture, which involves networking and communication, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The use of magneto-inductive communication transceivers involves electromagnetic fields, making cs.EM (Electromagnetics) a possible category. The paper also discusses the network topology of power transmitting active coils, which involves system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the potential for attaching the transceivers to everyday objects, which involves multimedia and human-computer interaction, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
